						<summary>

						<p>On the inner <hi rend="italic">gōpura,</hi> left of entrance, of the temple of Pālvaṇṇanāthasvāmi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikṛiti:</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record may be assigned on palaeographical grounds to c. 15th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record an order <hi rend="italic">(ōlai)</hi> of a king, whose name is not mentioned, granting 50 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> to meet the expenses of the daily worship and food offerings to the deity Ṉandīśvaram-uḍaiya-nayiṉār on the eleventh day in the month of Chittirai of the year Vikṛiti. The details of the grant portion are not clear. </p>						

						</summary>
